cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SE 

The paper discusses security mechanisms for Mobile Ad hoc Networks (MANETs), which are a subset of computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper specifically focuses on security issues, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed architecture involves clustering, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of Steganography and Cryptography suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) respectively.
